name: Zucchini Brownies
description: You will love these zucchini brownies! They're incredibly fudgy, chocolatey, perfectly sweet, and entirely vegan. All you need is 10 minutes of active preparation time!
recipeIngredient: 1 cup brown sugar or coconut sugar
1  flax egg ((1 tablespoon ground flaxseeds + 3 tablespoons of water))

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat the oven to 350 °F. Make the flax egg: place the water and the ground flaxseeds in a small bowl and stir well. Let it sit until you make the cake batter. Grate the zucchini. Either use a handheld grater or food processor to grate the zuchini. Give them a quick squeeze.

recipeInstructions.text: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
recipeInstructions.name: Place all ingredients in a large bowl.

recipeInstructions.text: Line a baking pan with parchment paper and pour the batter into the baking pan. Bake for 25 minutes.
recipeInstructions.name: Line a baking pan with parchment paper and pour the batter into the baking pan. Bake for 25 minutes.

recipeInstructions.text: Roughly chop the dark chocolate and melt it either on the stovetop or in the microwave.
recipeInstructions.name: Roughly chop the dark chocolate and melt it either on the stovetop or in the microwave.

recipeInstructions.text: Let the brownies cool down for a bit. Roughly chop the walnuts. Then add the melted dark chocolate on top and sprinkle with the chopped walnuts. Let the brownies cool down completely before cutting them into squares.
